    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Pete Crow-Armstrong** as our standout offensive engine. His elite score of 79.98 is fueled by a massive +18% adjustment for the matchup against Merrill Kelly, complemented by a +14% dynamic platoon edge and a +4% boost due to the starter's slow delivery, which provides a high-probability environment for him to exploit the league's scarcity in stolen bases. **Junior Caminero** remains a primary focal point in the middle of our lineup; despite a slight park penalty, his +15% SP skill adjustment against Tyler Mahle positions him as a high-upside play. Meanwhile, **Trea Turner** provides his usual stability at the top of the order, and **Colt Keith** benefits from a rare combination of strong platoon positioning and a favorable matchup against a pitcher susceptible to the stolen base, making them both essential anchors in today's 5x5 pursuit.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision involved **Jerar Encarnacion**, who sat on the cusp of the lineup with a score of 42.40. While his platoon advantage against Steven Matz was promising, he failed to clear the threshold required to displace our high-floor starters, ultimately falling victim to a lower projected efficiency than the depth currently rostered. We are keeping a close eye on **Hyeseong Kim**, whose score of 55.71 is buoyed by favorable wind conditions and a platoon edge, though his low batting position limits his run-scoring ceiling. Managers should note that while **Yordan Alvarez** faces a tougher L/L matchup, his elite xwOBA of 0.430 makes him a locked-in asset despite the platoon suppression. We continue to monitor the health of **Christian Yelich**, who remains on the IL, while **Josh Smith** and **Luke Raley** are held in reserve today as they failed to meet our internal efficiency requirements for a start.",
